an anti-inflammatory

29:58.798 --> 29:59.897
To ease the swelling.

29:59.899 --> 30:01.098
He's sedated
and comfortable.

30:01.100 --> 30:02.800
I don't get it.

30:02.802 --> 30:05.102
Look it,
the x-rays look normal.

30:05.104 --> 30:07.337
I have no idea what's
causing these manifestations.

30:07.339 --> 30:09.072
What about the head c.T.
Shahir ran?

30:09.074 --> 30:10.841
Absolutely clear.

30:10.843 --> 30:14.278
Let me bring it up
anyway.
Go for it.

30:18.216 --> 30:19.850
It's normal.
Yeah.

30:19.852 --> 30:22.853
No skull contusions,
no cranial swelling.

30:22.855 --> 30:23.954
(sighs)
hold on.

30:23.956 --> 30:25.455
What's that?

30:28.059 --> 30:30.160
He has a sternoclavicular
joint dislocation.

30:30.162 --> 30:32.462
Okay, so, we didn't
paralyze his vocal cords,

30:32.464 --> 30:33.964
And his wife isn't
trying to kill him.

30:33.966 --> 30:35.299
His ex-wife.

30:37.001 --> 30:39.503
(monitor beeping steadily)

30:39.505 --> 30:42.472
This stuff is like tar.

30:42.474 --> 30:43.574
Scar tissue and mucus.

30:43.576 --> 30:46.476
It's like
biological superglue.

30:46.478 --> 30:50.047
I can't see where his lungs end
and his ribcage begins.

30:50.049 --> 30:51.615
Damn it!

30:51.617 --> 30:54.151
I nicked a vessel.
Suction.

30:54.153 --> 30:57.120
(suction gurgles)

31:02.861 --> 31:04.194
Okay, we're good.

31:04.196 --> 31:06.063
